    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> (not a mustard fan? Go easy!) and <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>mustard dressing</strong></p><p>Once the sauce has thickened, stir through the <strong>chopped basil </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato & basil sauce</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>baby leaf salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
